{
  "texts": [
    "The higher the concreteness of the Law360 article, the higher the concreteness of the complaint generated therefrom.",
    "This paper tests whether GPT-3.5 can correctly determine which federal U.S. laws are potentially being violated from a given fact pattern.",
    "Overall, GPT-3.5's ability to determine potential violations of U.S. law from a given set of facts was poor.",
    "The primary reason for the low overall performance metrics was the high number of false negatives (i.e., violations it missed which were charged in the complaint).",
    "Because of this, the precision scores tended to be much higher than the other performance metrics."
  ]
}